This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D medical image registration using a convolutional neural network. It also involves unsupervised learning, which could place it in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of penalty loss and investigation of hyper-parameters suggests a focus on optimization and algorithm design, which could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the use of a neural network for registration suggests a focus on neural engineering (cs.NE).
